Arrow Electronics Elects Stephen C. Patrick to Its Board of Directors | Business Wire


























































Arrow Electronics Elects Stephen C. Patrick to Its Board of Directors






July 22, 2003 09:17 AM Eastern Daylight Time



				MELVILLE, N.Y.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--July 22, 2003--Arrow Electronics, Inc. (NYSE:ARW) today announced that Stephen C. Patrick, 53, has joined its Board of Directors. Mr. Patrick will be an independent director, continuing Arrow's commitment to maintain a substantial majority of independent directors on its Board.  "In today's environment, the commitment of outstanding and independent directors is more important than ever, and we are thrilled to welcome Mr. Patrick to our Board of Directors," stated William E. Mitchell, President and Chief Executive Officer of Arrow. "His broad based business experience, both domestic and international, and extensive finance background make him a valuable addition to our Board." 

 Mr. Patrick is Chief Financial Officer of the Colgate-Palmolive Company (NYSE:CL), a leading consumer products company with 2002 sales of $9.3 billion and a market capitalization of $31 billion, whose products in Oral, Personal, and Household Care and Pet Nutrition are manufactured and marketed in over 200 countries.  Mr. Patrick joined Colgate-Palmolive from Price Waterhouse in 1982. After various positions of increasing responsibility, Mr. Patrick was promoted to Colgate-Palmolive Company's Chief Financial Officer in 1996.  Mr. Patrick, who is a CPA in the state of Connecticut, received his Bachelor's Degree from the City University of New York and his Master's Degree from the University of Rhode Island. He is Vice President of the Financial Accounting Foundation (Trustees for the Financial Accounting Standards Board).  Arrow Electronics is one of the world's largest distributors of electronic components and computer products and a leading provider of services to the electronics industry. Headquartered in Melville, New York, Arrow serves as a supply channel partner for more than 600 suppliers and over 150,000 original equipment manufacturers, contract manufacturers, and commercial customers through more than 190 sales facilities and 21 distribution centers in 40 countries. Detailed information about Arrow's operations can be found at www.arrow.com.


